<h2 id="section-top">Teenage and young adult cancer services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=1063">The Royal Marsden NHS Foundation Trust</a>
</p>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent62cda6b69c324ae8a84edac11e4aeee5">
</div>
<p>Our new unit opens in 2011, but we already have an established team of experts (both medical and support services, e.g. dietitians and physiotherapists) who work with TYA patients wherever they are treated at The Royal Marsden, as well as in local hospitals and the community.<br/><br/>Our service includes expert medical and nursing care to ensure the best possible cancer treatment and supportive care. Your diagnosis, treatment and care will be coordinated by two teams of experts (known as a multidisciplinary team or MDT) who work very closely together; one team will manage your medical treatment and care, and the other will manage supportive, social, education, employment and psychological care for you and those close to you. You will be given the name of a member of staff (known as a key worker) who will be your point of contact at the hospital and will help you through diagnosis, treatment and after-care.<br/><br/>We also have Youth Support Worker who coordinates a programme of activities and events so that patients of a similar age can get together. These events have included trips to concerts, recording a song, pamper days, shopping trips to TopShop, outings to restaurants in local areas and bowling.<br/><br/>We also offer a drop-in support group for parents once a month.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>Visiting hours and what you need bring vary in each of the clinical areas. Information about how the hospital works and what you can bring in for each department will be sent to you before your first appointment and offered to you as required.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-serviceteamsummary">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear"><h3><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=9664">Staff</a></h3>
<div id="imageContent286ac6b3948349e3a3a48b1af3211449">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Team of healthcare professionals" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_TeamSummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=466"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>Your care will be jointly coordinated and managed by experts in your  cancer type and the teenager and young adult (TYA) team. The team  includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Medical consultants experienced in TYA cancer care who will link  with other specialists for your cancer type as needed</li>
<li>Consultant in TYA palliative and complex symptom care</li>
<li>Nurse consultant in TYA cancer care</li>
<li>Dietitians</li>
<li>Physiotherapist</li>
<li>Occupational therapist</li>
<li>Psychologists</li>
<li>CLIC Sargent social worker</li>
<li>Teenage Cancer Trust activity coordinator</li>
<li>Speech and language therapist</li>
<li>Clinical nurse specialist in outreach and symptom care</li>
<li>Teacher</li>
<li>Chaplain</li>
</ul>
<p>At The Royal Marsden we have access to a wide pool of high-quality  expertise to consult or involve in your cancer care. We are also able to  link with services closer to your home.</p>
<p>You, and those important to you, will be involved in your  decision-making, planning and care throughout diagnosis, treatment and  beyond.</p><p><a href="/Services/hospitals/Services/Service/Team/DefaultView.aspx?id=9664">Learn more about our staff</a></p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
